34:52.048 --> 34:54.050
Hey. What's going on in here?

34:54.050 --> 34:56.469
Watson, MC Autocat.

34:56.469 --> 34:58.096
Autocat...
(roars)

34:58.096 --> 34:59.347
...Watson.

34:59.347 --> 35:02.350
Like Pandasalt, Autocat
is an EDM artist

35:02.350 --> 35:04.519
who prefers
to remain anonymous.

35:04.519 --> 35:06.229
She's also
a trained musicologist

35:06.229 --> 35:07.981
and she's helping me
identify Pandasalt

35:07.981 --> 35:11.192
by playing known artists
with similar styles.

35:11.192 --> 35:13.945
You think one of them
is Pandasalt?

35:13.945 --> 35:16.448
Well, so far, we've reviewed
some promising candidates.

35:18.158 --> 35:20.160
WATSON: Wait, I
know this song.

35:20.160 --> 35:23.830
I was listening to some of, uh,
Pandasalt's music last night.

35:26.207 --> 35:27.792
It sounds like
one of his songs.

35:27.792 --> 35:29.544
Something about trash,
or something.

35:29.544 --> 35:31.588
(roars)

35:33.340 --> 35:34.966
âª Trash panda âª

35:34.966 --> 35:36.843
âª I got rights... âª

35:36.843 --> 35:39.387
Yep, almost
exactly the same.

35:39.387 --> 35:40.764
âª Veranda âª

35:40.764 --> 35:42.223
âª Hear my propaganda âª

35:42.223 --> 35:44.100
âª Trash panda, trash... âª

35:44.100 --> 35:47.062
It's a Long Island DJ
called Amos Deukmejian.

35:47.062 --> 35:49.147
I'd say we have our panda,
wouldn't you?

35:49.147 --> 35:51.358
